There is some problem with Regexp::Common which is independent from EPIC. It can be illustrated by the fact that the following code fails:

use Regexp::Common;
use Data::Dumper;

print Dumper\(\%RE\);

EPIC tries something similiar when retrieving the variable values from the 'main' package. I fixed it in 0.6.9 to tolerate the failure of retrieving a single variable. Thus, you will now see an entry named Error\(RE\) in the Variables view, but the values of all other variables should appear as expected.

