The "Extract subroutine" refactoring mishandles
single-quoted strings.  In the generated subroutine
they are all backslashed.

This:

my @bar = \(\);
push\(@bar, 'boo'\);

\------------

Is turned into this:

my @bar = \(\);
my \(\) = extracted \(\@bar\);

sub extracted \{
my $bar = shift;

push\(
@$bar, \'boo\'\);
return \(\);
\}

\---------------

Note also that the "return \(\)" statement is unnecessary.

